%I A183635 #24 Jun 22 2026 17:14:27
%S A183635 136,340,952,2884,9256,31060,107992,386404,1415176,5281780,20015032,
%T A183635 76773124,297329896,1160228500,4554034072,17956283044,71047145416,
%U A183635 281857767220,1120444917112,4460833796164,17780522733736,70933703913940,283169755256152,1130984041152484,4518851627646856
%N A183635 Number of (n+1) X 3 0..3 arrays with every 2 X 2 subblock summing to 6.
%C A183635 Conjecture: Number of (n+1) X (k+1) 0..p arrays with every 2 X 2 subblock summing to 2p is Sum_{i=1..(p+1)} i^(n+1)*(p+2-i)^(k+1) - 2*Sum_{i=1..p} i^(n+1)*(p+1-i)^(k+1) + Sum_{i=1..(p-1)} i^(n+1)*(p-i)^(k+1). - _Zhuorui He_, Jun 20 2026
%H A183635 Zhuorui He, <a href="/A183635/b183635.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a> (first 200 terms from R. H. Hardin)
%H A183635 Christian Krause, <a href="/A183635/a183635.txt">Proof of formula</a>, Jun 20 2026
%H A183635 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (10,-35,50,-24).
%F A183635 a(n) = 10*a(n-1) - 35*a(n-2) + 50*a(n-3) - 24*a(n-4).
%F A183635 From _Colin Barker_, Mar 31 2018: (Start)
%F A183635 G.f.: 4*x*(34 - 255*x + 578*x^2 - 384*x^3) / ((1 - x)*(1 - 2*x)*(1 - 3*x)*(1 - 4*x)).
%F A183635 a(n) = 18 + 3*2^(3+n) + 2*3^(2+n) + 4^(1+n).
%F A183635 (End) [proved by _Christian Krause_, Jun 20 2026]
%e A183635 Some solutions for 5 X 3:
%e A183635   2 2 0    0 0 1    1 2 1    1 2 0    0 3 0    3 0 1    3 1 2
%e A183635   0 2 2    3 3 2    0 3 0    2 1 3    1 2 1    0 3 2    1 1 2
%e A183635   2 2 0    0 0 1    1 2 1    1 2 0    2 1 2    2 1 0    3 1 2
%e A183635   0 2 2    3 3 2    3 0 3    0 3 1    3 0 3    0 3 2    1 1 2
%e A183635   3 1 1    0 0 1    0 3 0    1 2 0    3 0 3    3 0 1    1 3 0
%t A183635 A183635[n_] := 18 + 3*2^(n+3) + 2*3^(n+2) + 4^(n+1);
%t A183635 Array[A183635, 25] (* _Paolo Xausa_, Jun 22 2026 *)
%o A183635 (PARI) f(n, k, p)=sum(i=1, p+1, i^(n+1)*(p+2-i)^(k+1))-2*sum(i=1, p, i^(n+1)*(p+1-i)^(k+1))+sum(i=1, p-1, i^(n+1)*(p-i)^(k+1)) \\ f(n, k, p) is conjectured to be number of (n+1) X (k+1) 0..p arrays with every 2 X 2 subblock summing to 2p.
%o A183635 A183635(n) = f(n, 2, 3) \\ This is proved using the proved formula above.
%o A183635 \\ _Zhuorui He_, Jun 20 2026
